    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - 12/06/1994 and After - CONTROL ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1601601" svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>CONTROL ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>All major functions of the A/C-heater system are controlled from the cab control assembly (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1601602">Figure 2</hotlnk>). It includes three rotary knobs and an "ON/OFF" push button A/C
            switch. The center knob operates the blend door. The left knob controls the split between defrost and cab
            air by closing and opening a door located in the top of the unit assembly. The right knob is the fan switch
            and has three settings: LOW, MEDIUM and HIGH (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1601602">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f1601602" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1601602" filename="../figg16/G1601602.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="152px"/>
            <caption>Figure 2. Cab Control Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The driver floor dump door is controlled from the instrument panel. The passenger heat dump is fixed
            open.
        </para>
